# ggen-constitution-pack ontology — admitted-semantics mirror of
# .specify/memory/constitution.md v2.0.0 ("ggen Constitution", ratified
# 2025-12-11, last amended 2026-07-19).
#
# One ccn:Law individual per numbered Core Principle (I-XIV, 14 total).
# Each carries:
#   ccn:principleNumber / ccn:principleLabel  — identity, matches the prose doc
#   ccn:statement    — the principle's own language (faithful paraphrase;
#                       canonical Japanese terms kept verbatim per Principle
#                       XIII: 原語保持 / 訳語非権威 / 変換保存 / 差異受領 / 意味停止)
#   ccn:enforcedBy   — real file:line anchors, re-verified 2026-07-19 by
#                       reading the cited files directly (not asserted)
#   ccn:provenBy     — real test function names / real gate files found by
#                       grep 2026-07-19; absent where none exists
#   ccn:mechanized   — true ONLY where a real enforcing test/gate was found
#                       live; false with an honest ccn:note otherwise
#
# Per Principle XI/XII: a claim without evidence is refused; this file
# follows that discipline against itself. Two mechanized=false findings are
# not mere gaps but active divergences from the constitution's own prose,
# surfaced rather than hidden (Principle XIV Governance: "the disagreement
# is itself a defect to resolve -- neither silently wins"):
#   - Law VII: `crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs:1857` hardcodes
#     `andon: Andon::Green` unconditionally in `write_receipt`, contradicting
#     the "derived, never asserted" requirement in the live pipeline today.
#   - Law XII: the constitution's own prose (line 252) cites a test named
#     `reasoner_independence_e2e` as proving SPARQL-gate engine-independence;
#     no such test function exists anywhere in the workspace (grepped
#     2026-07-19, zero matches) -- the citation itself is unverified.
# Both are marked mechanized=false below with the specific note, not
# papered over.

@prefix ccn:  <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/ggen-constitution#> .
@prefix rdf:  <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

ccn:Law
    a            rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label   "Law" ;
    rdfs:comment "A numbered Core Principle from .specify/memory/constitution.md v2.0.0 (14 total)." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# I. Crate-First Architecture
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawI
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Crate-First Architecture" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "I" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Crate-First Architecture" ;
    ccn:statement      "Every feature MUST start as a standalone crate within the workspace: self-contained (no circular dependencies between workspace crates, verified at compile time), independently testable (80%+ coverage per crate), clearly scoped (single responsibility), documented (rustdoc on public APIs), consolidation-ready. If extracting a new crate creates a cycle, do NOT extract -- accept the module staying in its host crate with documented scope instead." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "Cargo.toml (root) [workspace] members array -- circular workspace-crate dependencies are rejected by cargo's own dependency resolver at compile time, before any ggen-specific check runs" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "Compile-time cycle rejection is real (rustc/cargo), but no dedicated ggen-side proving test was found by grep 2026-07-19 (crates/praxis-graphlaw/tests/*circular* tests found are unrelated business-logic/state-machine simulations, not a workspace-dependency-cycle proof). Pending." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# II. Infrastructure-Domain Separation (incl. Process-Intelligence Boundary)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawII
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Infrastructure-Domain Separation" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "II" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Infrastructure-Domain Separation" ;
    ccn:statement      "Engine code (ggen-engine and its kernel crates) MUST maintain clear boundaries between infrastructure (RDF graph management, the five-stage sync pipeline, template resolution/rendering, write-decision law, receipt chain, error taxonomy) and domain (pack management, capability registry, validation policies, marketplace). Process-Intelligence Boundary (CRITICAL): ggen EMITS process evidence (OCEL events); it does NOT analyse it -- discovery/conformance/fitness/precision/variants belong to wasm4pm/wasm4pm-compat. Analysis code found in ggen is post-split residue and MUST be deleted." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "scripts/ci/guard-process-intelligence-boundary.sh (greps for praxis_graphlaw::chatman and bcinr_powl(_receipt):: references outside praxis-core/praxis-graphlaw's own internals); wired into just pre-commit at justfile:357-358 (guard-process-intelligence-boundary recipe)" ;
    ccn:provenBy       "scripts/ci/guard-process-intelligence-boundary.sh (real shell-script CI guard, part of the 9-gate just pre-commit chain)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     true .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# III. Deterministic RDF Projections
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawIII
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Deterministic RDF Projections" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "III" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Deterministic RDF Projections" ;
    ccn:statement      "Code generation MUST be deterministic and reproducible: same input -> same output; every template SPARQL block MUST carry ORDER BY (enforced as FM-TPL diagnostics); Cargo.lock committed, pack content hash-locked in ggen.lock; generated outputs BLAKE3-hashed into the sync receipt; a second sync MUST be byte-identical on content, only the receipt chain advances (proven per consumer by sync-twice-diff, the guard-pack-proofs convention)." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "crates/ggen-config/src/manifest/validation.rs:119 (E0011, CONSTRUCT lacks ORDER BY), :189 and :337 (E0013, SELECT lacks ORDER BY), :480 (fn query_has_order_by, the textual ORDER BY check); crates/ggen-engine/tests/cli_boundary.rs:237 (sync_run_second_invocation_is_idempotent); crates/ggen-engine/tests/dogfood_regression.rs:63 (ggen_regenerates_route_files_byte_identically)" ;
    ccn:provenBy       "sync_run_second_invocation_is_idempotent (crates/ggen-engine/tests/cli_boundary.rs:237); ggen_regenerates_route_files_byte_identically (crates/ggen-engine/tests/dogfood_regression.rs:63)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     true ;
    ccn:note           "Idempotency/byte-identity is proven by the two cited tests. The E0011/E0013 ORDER BY-rejection code itself is confirmed live at the cited lines, but no dedicated #[test] fn asserting an E0011/E0013 refusal was found by grep 2026-07-19 in validation.rs (only general validate_* tests at lines 519-590 exist, none order-by-specific) -- that narrower sub-claim is unproven." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IV. Chicago TDD (Zero Tolerance)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawIV
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Chicago TDD (Zero Tolerance)" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "IV" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Chicago TDD (Zero Tolerance)" ;
    ccn:statement      "Test-Driven Development using Chicago School methodology is MANDATORY: state-based testing, real collaborators (actual engines, real files, real subprocess boundaries -- CliHarness), Red-Green-Refactor, 80%+ coverage on critical paths, reference oracles over hand-written assertions where a real independently-authored reference implementation exists (byte-identical copied test suites, the TCPS method). Exemption: test code MAY use unwrap()/expect() to fail fast on setup issues." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "crates/ggen-cheat-scanner/src/lib.rs (CHEAT-T01 vacuous-assert, CHEAT-T02 tautological-result-check, CHEAT-T03 no-assertion-test, CHEAT-T04 mock-import detectors); wired into just pre-commit via guard-cheat-scan at justfile:377-378" ;
    ccn:provenBy       "cheat_t01_vacuous_assert_flags_positive_fixture, cheat_t02_tautological_result_check_flags_positive_fixture, cheat_t03_no_assertion_test_flags_positive_fixture, cheat_t04_mock_import_flags_positive_fixture, cheat_t04_mock_substitute_flags_cross_file_positive_pair (all in crates/ggen-cheat-scanner/tests/scanner_test.rs)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     true ;
    ccn:note           "guard-cheat-scan currently fails on ~464 pre-existing findings across the workspace (tracked as TECH-DEBT-001, not blocking new work) -- the detector is real and live, the workspace is not yet clean under it." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# V. just Protocol
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawV
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "just Protocol" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "V" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "just Protocol" ;
    ccn:statement      "Direct cargo and cargo make invocations are PROHIBITED as entry points in development and CI. Use just recipes exclusively (just check, just test-lib/just test, just lint, just pre-commit, just verify-tcps, just docs-sync). Makefile.toml is historical reference only. Bare cargo remains acceptable inside recipes and for narrow local iteration, never as the gate." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "justfile (root) -- all gated tasks defined as just recipes; e.g. pre-commit: justfile:328" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "The justfile itself is real and is the actual entry point in practice, but no automated guard was found (grep 2026-07-19) that refuses a bare `cargo test`/`cargo build` invocation outside `just` -- this is convention plus documentation (CLAUDE.md, .claude/rules/), not a mechanically enforced gate. Pending." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VI. Type-First Thinking
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawVI
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Type-First Thinking" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "VI" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Type-First Thinking" ;
    ccn:statement      "Leverage Rust's type system for compile-time guarantees: express invariants in types (newtypes, enums, typestates make invalid states unrepresentable), zero-cost abstractions (generics/const generics over trait objects in hot paths), explicit ownership, type-safe AND ergonomic public APIs. The TCPS reference (生産線<稼働中> halting on 品質判定::異常) is the canonical in-repo demonstration." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "the Rust compiler itself (type-checking is unconditional for any code that compiles); packs/tcps-core-pack's generated 品質.rs / 全体.rs (typestate demonstration cited by name in the constitution)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "This is a design discipline enforced only by ordinary Rust type-checking, not by a dedicated ggen-specific gate or proving test found by grep 2026-07-19. Pending a concrete lint/gate if one is ever added." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VII. Andon Signal Protocol
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawVII
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Andon Signal Protocol" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "VII" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Andon Signal Protocol" ;
    ccn:statement      "Stop the line immediately when quality signals appear (RED: compiler error/test failure/gate refusal -- stop all work; YELLOW: warning/lint/incomplete evidence -- investigate before release; GREEN: safe to continue). Receipt andon MUST be derived, never asserted: a receipt's andon field MUST be computed from the admission decision over the evidence (all required evidence current and admitted -> Green; incomplete/unsupported -> Yellow; red/stale/inconsistent/refused -> Red). A synchronization event completing is an observation; it does not by itself produce Green." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs:1857 (write_receipt constructs ReceiptRecord)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "ACTIVE DIVERGENCE, not merely unproven: crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs:1857 currently hardcodes `andon: Andon::Green` unconditionally inside write_receipt, regardless of evidence, obligations, or admission outcome -- the exact opposite of 'derived, never asserted'. This is the concrete gap the constitution's own Sync Impact Report names as pending the receipt-v2 epoch migration (Center 2, a separate ongoing workflow phase). Falsely marking this true would itself be the Principle XI violation this pack exists to prevent." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VIII. Error Handling Standards
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawVIII
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Error Handling Standards" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "VIII" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Error Handling Standards" ;
    ccn:statement      "Production code MUST use Result<T, E> error handling: NO unwrap()/expect() in production (test code exempted); typed refusals (every refusal carries a stable [FM-<FAMILY>-NNN] code with remediation text); unknown is not success (unknown config keys, legacy law surfaces, unreadable governing inputs, malformed packs refuse loudly); fail-safe design (errors propagate with ? or are handled explicitly; unwrap_or_default() on a meaningful Result is a defect)." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "crates/chicago-tdd-tools/src/lib.rs:125-129 (#![deny(clippy::unwrap_used)], #![deny(clippy::expect_used)], #![deny(clippy::panic)], #![deny(clippy::todo)], #![deny(clippy::unimplemented)])" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "The `deny(clippy::unwrap_used)` lint gate is real but confirmed only in chicago-tdd-tools (a dev/test-only helper crate), not in ggen-engine, ggen-cli, or ggen-config themselves (grep 2026-07-19 found no matching `deny` attribute in those crates' lib.rs). A parallel grep found 23 `unwrap()` call sites in crates/ggen-engine/src/*.rs outside test modules. The FM-<FAMILY>-NNN typed-refusal convention is real and widely used (e.g. FM-WRITE-002/004/005/006, FM-PACK-008/012/013, FM-CHAIN-2/8/9 all confirmed live in crates/ggen-engine/src). Overall principle: partially real, not fully mechanized workspace-wide. Pending." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IX. Concurrent Execution
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawIX
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Concurrent Execution" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "IX" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Concurrent Execution" ;
    ccn:statement      "All operations MUST be batched in single messages ('1 MESSAGE = ALL RELATED OPERATIONS'): task tracking, agent spawning, file operations, commands. Parallel agent execution: fan-out implementation batches concurrently; verification is a distinct sequential phase (implementers' self-reports are inputs, not proof -- Principle XI). File organization: NEVER save working files to the repo root." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     ".claude/rules/_core/absolute.md (rule 1: Concurrent Operations, rule 2: No Root Files); packs/claude-code-pack's generated implement-verify workflow shape" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "This is an agent-operating-procedure convention documented in .claude/rules, not a mechanically enforced gate against the repo's file/git state -- no test or CI check was found by grep 2026-07-19 that verifies message-batching or root-file placement after the fact. Pending." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# X. Lean Six Sigma Quality
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawX
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Lean Six Sigma Quality" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "X" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Lean Six Sigma Quality" ;
    ccn:statement      "Enforce manufacturing-grade quality standards: Poka-Yoke (invalid states unrepresentable in types; gates refuse before write); 9-gate pre-commit (just pre-commit chains fmt-check, check, lint, test-lib, coherence-check, guard-process-intelligence-boundary, guard-cheat-scan, guard-claims-schema, guard-pack-proofs -- all green or the commit does not happen; a partial pass is a failure); cheat scanning (ggen-cheat-scanner detects vacuous asserts, tautological checks, no-assertion tests, mock imports); evidence over narration (no completion claim without the command run and its exit code)." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "justfile:328 (pre-commit: fmt-check check lint test-lib coherence-check guard-process-intelligence-boundary guard-cheat-scan guard-claims-schema guard-pack-proofs -- the literal 9-gate recipe dependency chain)" ;
    ccn:provenBy       "justfile pre-commit recipe (justfile:328-331, all 9 gate names present verbatim); guard-cheat-scan recipe (justfile:377-378, cargo run --quiet -p ggen-cheat-scanner)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     true .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# XI. Admission Boundary & Standing (Law 14)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawXI
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Admission Boundary & Standing (Law 14)" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "XI" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Admission Boundary & Standing (Law 14)" ;
    ccn:statement      "自己申告は観測であり、standing ではない。 Self-reports are observations, not standing. A claim alone cannot cross the admission boundary; evidence alone cannot either -- evidence is evaluated under this constitution and the durable consequence is receipted: observation -> evidence -> constitutional judgment -> standing ceiling -> next lawful generation. Receipts MUST carry observational truth and constitutional truth without confusing them. Standing is a ceiling (meet of lifecycle x scope x equivalence x freshness), never the most impressive passing cell. Maturity (L1-L5) is derived from named artifacts only; a self-reported level contradicted by its own evidence is refused. Receipt epochs migrate by law, not by field addition: no backfilling of knowledge that did not exist." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "crates/praxis-core/src/receipt_record.rs (ReceiptRecord, chain_hash_hex/prev_chain_hash_hex/signature_hex); crates/ggen-engine/src/sync.rs:1778-1864 (write_receipt)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "The receipt-chain plumbing (chain_hash_hex, prev_chain_hash_hex, signature_hex) is real and live, but the epoch-migration machinery this principle demands (new epoch identity, migration receipt, dual-read/single-write compatibility, LegacyObserved recovery ceiling) does not exist yet -- pending the receipt v2 epoch migration (Center 2), a separate ongoing workflow phase per the task instructions for this pack. Marking this mechanized=true would itself be the exact self-certification failure Law 14 forbids." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# XII. Evidence as Law
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawXII
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Evidence as Law" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "XII" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Evidence as Law" ;
    ccn:statement      "Verification results are admitted graph facts enforced by refusal gates, not attention-dependent shell rituals. Admission gates are SPARQL (gates/*.rq: a # MESSAGE: header + one ASK/SELECT; violation = typed FM-PACK-012/013 refusal). External check results enter the graph through the same admission path as all law. Four-process separation: observation / evidence transport / judgment / manufacture. Generated output is never authoritative input unless explicitly readmitted. Every reflexive layer bottoms out in external ground truth (a real exit code, a byte-identity against a frozen reference, a second-engine agreement)." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "packs/ggen-verify-pack/gates/010_evidence_present.rq, 020_evidence_green.rq, 030_evidence_fresh.rq, 040_latest_andon_green.rq, 050_output_count_regression.rq (all real SPARQL ASK/SELECT gate files, each carrying a # MESSAGE: header)" ;
    ccn:provenBy       "packs/ggen-verify-pack/gates/*.rq (5 real gate files, confirmed by direct read 2026-07-19)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     true ;
    ccn:note           "Opt-in: these gates only fire when a consumer sets [law] reflexive = true. Also flagging a divergence: the constitution's own prose (line 252 of .specify/memory/constitution.md) cites a test named `reasoner_independence_e2e` as proving engine-independence (praxis-graphlaw vs Oxigraph agreement) for these gates -- grep across the whole workspace 2026-07-19 found zero matches for that function name. That specific sub-claim is unverified as written; the gates themselves are real." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# XIII. Canonical Vocabulary (原語保持)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawXIII
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Canonical Vocabulary (原語保持)" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "XIII" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Canonical Vocabulary (原語保持)" ;
    ccn:statement      "Canonical production vocabulary participates in the architecture; it is not localization. 原語保持: canonical production concepts (自働化, 現地現物, 受領証, 異常停止, 標準作業, 改善, かんばん, ポカヨケ, ...) retain their original terms throughout the normative manufacturing surface. 訳語非権威: translations may aid comprehension but possess no independent authority. 変換保存: every projection MUST preserve canonical vocabulary through graph union, serialization, generation, compilation, packaging, and replay -- proven by byte-fidelity oracles, not asserted. 差異受領: any unavoidable alteration is named, justified, bounded, and bound to a 受領証. 意味停止: when a transformation cannot preserve the concept, the process stops rather than emitting a convenient approximation." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "packs/tcps-core-pack/templates/ (24 Japanese-named .tmpl files, e.g. 自働化.rs.tmpl, 語彙.rs.tmpl, 品質.rs.tmpl, generating equally Japanese-named crates/tcps-core-style output files verbatim)" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "tcps-core-pack is real, live, existing evidence that canonical Japanese terms are preserved verbatim through generation (原語保持 in practice), but no dedicated byte-fidelity-oracle proving test for THIS principle specifically (as opposed to tcps-core-pack's own internal proofs) was found by grep 2026-07-19. Pending." .

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# XIV. Self-Hosting Governance
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
ccn:LawXIV
    a                  ccn:Law ;
    rdfs:label         "Self-Hosting Governance" ;
    ccn:principleNumber "XIV" ;
    ccn:principleLabel "Self-Hosting Governance" ;
    ccn:statement      "ggen is not the privileged exception to the laws it imposes. It becomes a product manufactured by its own packs through staged authority migration -- never in one leap: Descriptive mirror -> Generated secondary surfaces -> Generated decision surfaces -> Generated execution surfaces -> Self-hosting candidate -> Fixed point -> Reference retirement. The generation ladder: G0 (trusted seed) manufactures G1; fixed point requires stable closure across successive clean generations, equivalence declared per artifact class (byte/semantic/behavioral). No same-generation constitutional mutation: Constitution N governs Generation N+1. Independent rails: generated proofs alone never judge the generator." ;
    ccn:enforcedBy     "packs/ggen-constitution-pack itself (this pack, heal-thyself-r1) -- Stage 1 'Descriptive mirror' of the generation ladder in progress" ;
    ccn:mechanized     false ;
    ccn:note           "This pack's own existence is Stage-1 evidence (a descriptive mirror) of the ladder this principle describes, but no automated fixed-point-closure test or generation-ledger check exists yet to mechanically verify ladder-stage claims -- pending Center 2 and beyond, per the task instructions for this pack (a separate ongoing workflow phase)." .
